==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phonetic
<hw>Pho*net"ic</hw> <pr>(f⟦osl⟧*n⟦ecr⟧t"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>fwnhtiko`s</grk>, fr. <grk>fwnh`</grk> a sound, tone;
akin to Gr. <grk>fa`nai</grk> to speak: cf. F.
<ets>phon⟦eacute⟧tique</ets>. See <er>Ban</er> a proclamation.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the voice, or its use.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Representing sounds; <as>as, <ex>phonetic</ex>
characters</as>; -- opposed to <contr>ideographic</contr>; <as>as, a
<ex>phonetic</ex> notation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Phonetic spelling</b></col>, <cd>spelling in phonetic
characters, each representing one sound only; -- contrasted with
<contr>Romanic spelling</contr>, or that by the use of the Roman
alphabet.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phonetically</ent>⟦br⟧
